begin_memory_text: We talked about the places or states we currently live at, and about where else we have lived or moved to in the last few years.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my experience of becoming a US citizen. And we talked about my chat partner's son living in Washington State and that she hasn't seen her son since 4 years.
end_memory_text: We talked about the differences between the metric system and the imperial system. We also talked about different driving rules and compared a few driving rules from Germany and America.
rest_of_day_open: I like having a routine so every day is pretty much going to look the same. I will get up early in the morning, have breakfast and start working almost immediately after breakfast. critical_positive: The conversation started really well, I found my chat partner very likeable and we quickly found some interesting topics to talk about. There were virtually no gaps in during the conversation and each one of us had something to contribute to the conversation. Overall it was a very pleasant experience.
critical_negative: I can honestly not think of anything that didn't work so well. We had a pleasant conversation and even went overtime. As far as I remember we did not interrupt each other and let the other person always finish what they wanted to say. Overall the conversation worked very well, I have nothing to report that didn't work well.

begin_memory_text: We were happy to see each other and we talked about where we live. He said he lives in Missouri and I told him I live in North Carolina and he said he and his wife have wanted to visit NC because they have seen how pretty it is.
middle_memory_text: He said he is originally from Germany and that made me so happy because I am currently taking German in college. I told him I am studying German and I introduced myself in German and asked his name in German. We talked about the citizenship process as he became a U.S. citizen. We talked about where he lived in Germany (Cologne) and he described the location and the type of weather they have there.
end_memory_text: We talked about how long it has been since we have been able to see family members that live in other states or countries. We talked about the winter weather and what we like - both of us like a white Christmas. We talked a little about him teaching German online.
rest_of_day_open: I will be working on my German homework tomorrow because it is due on Thursday. I will go to campus for class on Thursday morning and then I will go take a hike somewhere if the weather is nice. critical_positive: My curiosity about Germany and his process of becoming a U. S. citizen worked well for our conversation, because it kept me asking questions which kept the conversation flowing. My conversation partner was friendly and willing to talk about his experiences so I think that was also helpful. Mutual respect was also advantageous to our successful and enjoyable conversation.
critical_negative: We both identified as introverts and I think at times we did have some lags in the conversation because we were not sure where to go next. I wish my conversation partner had asked me more questions. I also wish he had been willing to engage in speaking German with me as that is something I am learning right now and I would have really enjoyed speaking with a native speaker.
